      "writtenOn": "2021-02-04T22:35:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why not?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 487,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 487,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "bfc23d6a6a17ba7b698ed4f7fefedb23e1dfba42",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "39840cff_f368a4ca",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLPipelineStageCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T14:56:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Anything that\u0027s emitting SkSL that doesn\u0027t go into a function body has to be wrong - the strings built by this code are injected as function bodies by the FP. Basically, anything that\u0027s metadata about the shader, global declarations (variables, types, etc...) has to somehow be routed elsewhere or it ends up scoped incorrectly.",
      "parentUuid": "3a885939_b63527c3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 487,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 487,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "bfc23d6a6a17ba7b698ed4f7fefedb23e1dfba42",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "28396080_257c5a59",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLPipelineStageCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T15:00:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Wait... Runtime Effects can have (non-inlined) helper functions, can\u0027t they??\nIf we omit prototypes we run the risk of emitting function calls that haven\u0027t been declared.\n\n(I know in CPU mode the calls will be flattened out but in GPU mode, that\u0027s not guaranteed)",
      "parentUuid": "39840cff_f368a4ca",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 487,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 487,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "bfc23d6a6a17ba7b698ed4f7fefedb23e1dfba42",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a11d7e6e_481215b8",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLPipelineStageCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T15:10:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes. Today, as our conservative way of enforcing that recursion can\u0027t happen, we don\u0027t allow calls to undefined functions (in strictESMode). If we decide to relax that (and do an actual analysis of the call graph), we\u0027d need to handle this correctly. As it stands, I think that if you make a runtime effect with:\n\n  void foo();\n  void foo() { /* some code */ }\n\n  half4 main() {\n    foo();\n  }\n\n... and foo() doesn\u0027t get inlined, the declaration of foo() will get emitted into main\u0027s body. Testing now... yup.",
      "parentUuid": "28396080_257c5a59",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 487,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 487,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "bfc23d6a6a17ba7b698ed4f7fefedb23e1dfba42",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "15ce5b82_6108dc68",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLPipelineStageCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T15:12:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The upshot is that today we can fix this bug by just dropping function prototypes on the floor, because they\u0027re never necessary until we allow calling declared-but-not-defined functions.",
      "parentUuid": "a11d7e6e_481215b8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 487,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 487,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "bfc23d6a6a17ba7b698ed4f7fefedb23e1dfba42",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "66634231_3889c9ca",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLPipelineStageCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 5631
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T15:27:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Did this, and added a comment to explain the situation.",
      "parentUuid": "15ce5b82_6108dc68",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 487,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 487,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "bfc23d6a6a17ba7b698ed4f7fefedb23e1dfba42",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "87b062bd_3d804d6e",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLPipelineStageCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T15:47:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The inliner can arbitrarily move around function bodies, including function calls, so we need to be careful. But I\u0027m unable to think of a counterexample where this can actually break if you disallow prototypes.",
      "parentUuid": "66634231_3889c9ca",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 487,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 487,
        "endChar": 32
      },
